# Keep POSIX shell scripts LF-only on every platform.
#
# `install.sh` (and any other `*.sh`) carries a `#!/usr/bin/env sh` shebang. If a
# Windows clone with `core.autocrlf=true` rewrites it to CRLF, the trailing `\r`
# turns the interpreter into `sh\r` and the script fails to launch
# (`/usr/bin/env: 'sh\r': No such file or directory`) — exactly on the install
# path a newcomer hits first. Forcing `eol=lf` on `*.sh` keeps the bootstrap
# wrapper runnable in WSL / Git Bash / Linux / macOS regardless of the clone's
# autocrlf setting.
*.sh text eol=lf

# PowerShell is comfortable with either ending; leave it to the platform default.
*.ps1 text
